title: Independent  Candidate Muhammad Israr wins PK-68 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent Candidate Muhammad Israr has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-68 Mohmand-II by securing 20,690 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Jammiat Ulma E Islam Pakistan Hanif ul Zaman who bagged 12,156 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turn-out remained 24.41 per cent.
